    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Reaping What He Sows</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Guy Cherry letter says Nicholas D Kristof offers good suggestions to rescue his presidency, but fears Pres Bush will ignore them, leaving America seriously damaged (Dec 31, 2006, Op-Ed column)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Ten Suggestions for Rescuing the Bush Legacy,'' by Nicholas D. Kristof (column, Dec. 31):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Ten Suggestions for Rescuing the Bush Legacy,'' by Nicholas D. Kristof (column, Dec. 31):</p>
        <p>All good suggestions, Mr. Kristof. Unfortunately, President Bush will adopt none of them and will reap the legacy he sowed.</p>
        <p>America can only hope that the damage left by this president can be repaired over time.</p>
        <p>Guy Cherry  Beaverton, Ore., Dec. 31, 2006</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
